Attribution
================================================================================

This product contains software derived from the "ralph-loop" plugin
developed by Anthropic, PBC and distributed under the Apache License,
Version 2.0:

    https://github.com/anthropics/claude-plugins-official/tree/main/plugins/ralph-loop

The original ralph-loop plugin is Copyright Anthropic, PBC, licensed under
Apache License, Version 2.0. The Watchdog plugin keeps ralph-loop's core
mechanic (a Stop hook that re-feeds the user's prompt to drive a
self-referential iterative loop inside a single Claude Code session) and
introduces the following substantive modifications:

  - Replaced the <promise> XML-tag exit protocol with a headless
    Claude Haiku classifier that reads the current turn's tool_use
    invocations and decides whether any files were modified. This
    catches Bash-driven file mutations (sed -i, mv, > file, git add,
    etc.) that a tool-name whitelist would miss.

  - Added an exit precondition: the turn must have called at least
    one tool before the loop is allowed to exit. A pure-text response
    ("I've verified, all good") never terminates the loop, preventing
    the agent from claiming completion without doing real verification.

  - Hid the loop from the agent. The Stop hook emits no systemMessage,
    the setup script writes only the user's prompt to stdout, and all
    diagnostic output is routed to stderr. The agent has no way to
    tell it is running inside a loop and therefore cannot short-circuit
    by emitting a fake completion signal.

  - Introduced per-session state files keyed by TERM_SESSION_ID so
    concurrent watchdogs in different terminal tabs do not clobber
    each other's state. The state file format was also switched from
    markdown-with-YAML-frontmatter to JSON, parsed with jq.

  - Appended an English verification reminder to every re-fed prompt,
    instructing the agent to re-run the verification with real tool
    calls instead of answering from prior context or memory.

  - Fixed a transcript-parsing bug in the Stop hook where tool_result
    entries (which carry role=user in the JSONL transcript) were being
    mistaken for turn boundaries, causing the current turn's tool_use
    blocks to be excluded from the classification prompt.

Files significantly modified from their ralph-loop originals include:

  - hooks/stop-hook.sh
  - scripts/setup-watchdog.sh (originally scripts/setup-ralph-loop.sh)
  - scripts/stop-watchdog.sh  (originally scripts/cancel-ralph.sh)
  - commands/start.md         (originally commands/ralph-loop.md)
  - commands/stop.md          (originally commands/cancel-ralph.md)

See each file's header comment for a per-file attribution notice.
